\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t        \t\t\t\t\n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/amazon-fire-max-11-review/\" title=\"Amazon Fire Max 11 review\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\t\t\tAmazon Fire Max 11 review\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eAmazon\u0026#39;s most expensive tablet yet is held back by a pitiful app experience\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-amazon-fire-max-11\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Amazon Fire Max 11?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eThis is one of those tablets that usually doesn\u0026#39;t get a lot of love because, while it does run on Android, it\u0026#39;s \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/what-is-amazon-fire-os/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ea custom version created by Amazon\u003c/a\u003e, and also has its own app store and doesn\u0026#39;t rely on Google Play Services.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eNow, for the most part, Amazon has made great strides over the past several years, but it doesn\u0026#39;t have all the applications you\u0026#39;d find on the Google Play Store. With that said, the Fire Max 11 features a beautiful design, a fantastic 11-inch screen and plenty of power under the hood.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eWhen it comes to the specifics, this tablet runs a MediaTek MT8188J SoC that\u0026#39;s paired with 4GB of RAM and 64GB of internal storage. There\u0026#39;s also a microSD slot for storage expansion, and you can expect up to 14 hours of use with a single charge. In addition, it has a USB-C port, along with a 3.5mm audio jack.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eYou also get an 8MP camera on the front, and an 8MP camera on the rear. When it comes to connectivity, there\u0026#39;s Wi-Fi 6 and Bluetooth 5.3. Now, you also get a keyboard and stylus with this bundle, which means you can transform this tablet into a productivity machine if you wish.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eAnd for the price, it\u0026#39;s a pretty solid option if you\u0026#39;ve been looking for a new tablet. Of course, if you\u0026#39;re someone that lives in Google\u0026#39;s ecosystem, we probably \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/best-cheap-android-tablets/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003erecommend checking out some other tablets\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n                            \n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
